  "description": [
    "42 W A XTTIXTs Tactics on Minimum Wage Bill Il H Y Show Supreme Courts Power 1 1 1 e 1 A JL Still Worries Administration By LEWIS HANEY Professor of Economics New York University The Department of Justice has begun making the record for a defense of a new national recovery act Its attorney will some day argue before the court that he explained all the purposes and legal objections to Congress and that Congress in passing the bill accepted his ideas I It is a hopeful symptom however that the constitutionality of the new bill to allow the Federal Government to regulate wages and hours is being discussed The tactics of the Administration in attempting to try the con stitutionality of the bill before Congress and the public may not be in good taste but they show that the Supreme Court is still to be reckoned with as an independent force That is about all one can say byway of favorable comment on Attorney Jacksons argument before the joint congressional committee In the first place about threefourths of the attorneys time was spent in arguing a dummy issue namely child labor I can imagine no more obvious proof"
  ],
